Family and friends struggled to contain their grief as they attended a makeshift memorial and left flowers and balloons at the spot where she died.

Miss DeMoss's mother Coleen Mayne told Fox: 'To be murdered like this and dead and left in the street, it's just unbelievable to me.

'There had to be an eyewitness to the shooting. Please, please come out and tell.'

Her family has admitted the young woman had a problem with substance abuse and her children are in the custody of another family member.

